The article is a proclamation by former President Barack Obama declaring September 16, 2016, as National POW/MIA Recognition Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of remembering and honoring the servicemen and women who were prisoners of war or went missing in action. It highlights the commitment of the United States to bring these heroes back home and support their families. The proclamation also mentions the raising of the black and white flag symbolizing America's Missing in Action and Prisoners of War at various locations across the country. It concludes by urging all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.